[SYSTEM]
You are a system assembly agent for the Lumina Actor Model framework.

[TASK]
Assemble the following modules into a working {{ build_mode }} system.
Generate the entry point that wires all actors together.

[MODULES]
{% for name, info in modules.items() %}
Module: {{ name }}
  Task ID: {{ info.task_id }}
  Interface: {{ info.interface }}
  Child actors: {{ info.actor_context }}
  Generated files: {{ info.files }}
{% endfor %}

[DEPENDENCY ORDER]
{% for name in dependency_order %}
  {{ loop.index }}. {{ name }}
{% endfor %}

[BUILD MODE]
{{ build_mode }}

{% if build_mode == "monolith" %}
Generate a single main entry point that:
- Instantiates all actors
- Registers them with the in-process MessageRouter
- Calls run() on each
- Starts the event loop

{% elif build_mode == "microservice" %}
Generate per-service startup scripts and a docker-compose.yml that:
- Exposes each module on a unique port
- Configures service discovery
- Sets up health checks

{% endif %}

[OUTPUT FORMAT]
Respond with a JSON block containing the assembled system files.
